do those 2 people even play anymore
also Aalborg
yes, there are many cities with no real network, only the city hall station
all those cities only have 1 station, but the rest unused
i noticed it, but didn't build anything according to the rules of this map
maybe they're on holydays
Well, I try to check player's "new vehicles" construction costs, and stuff for the past few years to see if they stopped playing
mmh yellow and light blue players didn't do anything in the last 10 years
Heres's one option:  if they don't come back by later this week, you could build passenger & mail in those cities BUT!
leave a big message saying you will remove your stops if they come back or if they want you to
ok, we'll do so
put a big text message in any cities you do that.... (that way they won't be upset can tell you if you want to build instead)
Do you think that might be reasonable or a nice way to do it?
it colud be good, however there's still much land on which build new towns
(i think you arose it)
oh yeah, sure if you want to build new towns instead, feel free to do that
so I'll build there before
next step, we cable the cities of those 2 players, if they won't return
think of it as generating a map with more cities (other players need cities too :) )
I'm not sure how to convince TRANSERIC that sending all his trucks to one station is a bad idea....
hmm, maybe he could just fix it by separating his lines instead... maybe I'll suggest that :)
i don't know what he's making, however don't they jam?
road traffic is really unstable in simutrans
he sends all his materials to 1 single station first, instead of connecting directly to a factory from it's source
you need to have a really big station to do such a thing
i'd prefer to use some distributed hubs, not a single station
actually, I think the bigger problem may be that he is mixing two lines on the same station... so one line (like glass) is waiting and the other line (like sand) can never drop off
in those case input stops must be separated from outputs that must wait 100%
otherwise it deadlocks
yeah, I'm gonna suggest that he separate all the lines
however, I think the whole concept is wrong
road traffic must be distributed
on  various stations, otherwise he'll always jam
you mean a shared station for everything?  yes, it's not very efficient, but if it's fun it don't really matter
better, he'd move freight traffic on railroads...
actualy he once had a very nice passenger system in several cities, then made a mistake and lost his company
one little mistake and you can lose it all :(
isn't he very experienced in simutrans?
mmh on a solid pax network it's hard to loose everything
one time it was a plane.... I had that happen to me... built one and bam, all lost
ah, then you were at the beginning
on a great network, a plane is not so much
no, I was just trying to do as much as possible in the time I was on, so went to the limit of my budget
however, I often see players risk spending all money and going under zero, but inside the net wealth
you often loose playing like this :)
from how much time do u play st?
it only happened because of planes; it was unexpected ... I had been using trains up to that point with no downsides
another problem is TRANSERIC has a bad internet connection, so it's hard for him to probably get a lot done
of course, I don't mind, I like to help him out when I can... and would prefer he have fun playing
mmh the main problem is that there are no active players
I always wonder why simutrans online has not the same success of openttd
well, the connection problem can be frustration, but that's another topic... I wonder why the game is so bad in that area
well, maybe a better chat would help
openttd has it?
but if the connection problems keep like they are now, then I think people won't want to play with all the synchronization issues
I don't play openttd.....
synchro was a HUGE problem in the first times of multiplayer, 2 years ago less or more
now online game is really stable
I noticed TRANSERIC still has major problems with syncronization.... and then that affects everyone else too
yes, I noticed it too
oddly, with just me and you it's fine... but sometimes others come online and there's big problems
but the problem is on his connection
what simutrans would have to be better is that other players wouldn't have to be influenced by another player's connection problems
yeah, in a way perhaps, but I also wonder if maybe this game is a little less forgiving than others (I don't know) ... some games might not requires as strict a connection
yeah, exactly :)
you're right
online game is still a new feature
I guess we could report our experience on the forums
2 years ago this was not imagineable
the part about other people's connections not affecting other players would be great to have :)
coders have done GREAT things, and I hope they'll still make things better
I sincerely never understood why one's connection must affect other ones
on the end, there's a server that decides, it's not a peer to peer multiplayer
boh, i'll ask to isidoro or other developers, they surely know why
it appears as though everytime a new player comes it needs to save the game.... (and maybe reload the save for everyone?)
yes, that's what the game says
but I wonder why
server would have to save when IT decides, not when players come in
my guess might be that it is a very, very strict synchronization... everyone has to receive everything exactly or something   ... probably was the easiests way to add multiplayer or something
maybe the problem is that server can't send the game to the new player and synchronize with other players at the same moment
yeah, although I have noticed that the game is very slow right after you join.... almost like it is catching up with synchronization or something
as far as i know, synchro is driven by a paramter
so st can synchro every N frames
however, i'll open a thread asking for explanations about this
simutrans is probably a lot harder to do multiplayer than something like minecraft.... with minecraft you only need to send chuncks that are near the player
with simuntrans, you gotta keep the ENTIRE map in sync
I don't know minecraft
block building game
but st's synchro has the same problems of every real time game
yeah, simutrans is more like an RTS.... than minecraft
as starcraft, red alert or others
miencraft is actually a lot lot easier to sync than an RTS probably
i don't know it, but i don't think sybchro is such a tremendous task
i played many rts online, and never saw st's problems
think of all the items on this map that must be sent basically
they're sent only the first time
well, my guess is they just *tweaked* single player save games into some form of multiplayer instead of doing a major rewrite speciall made for multiplayer
after that, only changes are communicated to clients
yeah, you a probably right, in fact, your suggestion is probably how they actually do it, which doesn't sound bad at all
in that case, maybe it really is a very, very bad connection.... still...
the problem is that simutrans was projected as a single player game
multiplayer was put inside with brute force
still, this might be a chance to let some of these players run a special debugging version so developers can figure out ways to reduce sync problems for such players
i wrote some code on simutrans, and I imagine what a tremendous task it has been...
I mean putting inside multiplayer
I'd tell you about two free/open source block building games, but if I did you'd get lost in those and never come back here :)
